i## Basic Drone CI/CD		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iAfter setting up Drone, the next step is to add a task. Here I'll use		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe example of deploying my Hexo blog.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iI already have a set of deployment scripts for the following tasks:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Install node_modules		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `hexo generate`		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- `hexo deploy` to GitHub Pages (as a backup)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Convert all images to WebP, and Gzip and Brotli compress all static		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  resources		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Rsync generated files to all of my nodes with Ansible		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIn addition, since my blog uses Dependabot to update dependencies		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iautomatically, Dependabot may create pull requests from time to time.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iObviously, the pull requests shouldn't be deployed to my nodes. The CI		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ishould just try generating the files and see if it fails.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSo here comes the most basic form of our configuration, written to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i`.drone.yaml`:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```yaml		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ikind: pipeline		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
itype: docker		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iname: default		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
itrigger:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  branch:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    - master		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isteps:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - name: hexo generate		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    image: node:15-alpine		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    commands:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      # Not all packages are needed: this is to be consistent with following steps		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      - apk add --no-cache build-base bash git openssh wget python3		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        gzip brotli zstd parallel imagemagick		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      - npm install		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      - node_modules/hexo/bin/hexo generate		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - name: hexo deploy		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    image: node:15-alpine		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    commands:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      # Install packages		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      - apk add --no-cache build-base bash git openssh wget python3		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        gzip brotli zstd parallel imagemagick		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      - node_modules/hexo/bin/hexo deploy		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Don't deploy Dependabot's PRs		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    when:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      event:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        exclude:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i          - pull_request		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # Some subsequent steps are skipped		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThis config will generate the static files and attempt `hexo deploy`,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ibut it will fail since it doesn't have the SSH keys. For obvious		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ireason I won't recommend adding your SSH key directly to the config.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iYou should instead add it to Vault (or Drone's secret storage), and		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iuse it from the config file:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```yaml		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# Fetch SSH key from Vault, the repository must be set to Trusted in Drone		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ikind: secret		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iname: id_ed25519		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iget:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # This path is shown as kv/ssh in Vault. "data" must be added.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  path: kv/data/ssh		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  name: id_ed25519		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i---		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ikind: pipeline		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
itype: docker		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iname: default		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i# ...		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isteps:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  # ...		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - name: hexo deploy		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    image: node:15-alpine		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    environment:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      # Use the SSH key fetched from Vault, set as environment variable		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      SSH_KEY:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        from_secret: id_ed25519		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    commands:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
